  "body": "Hi! I'm Tei from Test in Prod, working on [op-erigon](https://github.com/testinprod-io/op-erigon).\r\n\r\nWhile merging erigon upstream into op-erigon, I noticed EIP-4844 blob TX was added to [erigon's latest release](https://github.com/ledgerwatch/erigon/releases/tag/v2.43.0).\r\n\r\nIt seems there's no spec about handling blob TX on L2, and blob TX is not yet merged to op-geth.\r\n\r\nIs blob TX supported on L2? if not, how should it be blocked? (e.g. return specific error code)\r\n\r\nI think it would be very helpful to exec-engine developers if there are specs for handling each EIP-2718 transaction type on L2.\r\n\r\nThank you!\r\n\r\n",
