    "body": "We probably should add this to the specs somewhere but the L2 execution engine (op-geth or op-erigon) should be configured to support the Paris hard fork (ie the merge) as a base with the additional functionality from the bedrock spec like deposit transactions added on.  As such, EIP-4844 and blob TX aren't supported on L2. The rejection should be done in the same way that current L1 mainnet does as EIP-4844 isn't active there yet either. Usually this kind of functionality is controlled by the fork schedule specified in the genesis config (or chain spec for clients that use those).",
